<doc id="1010430" wikidata="Q363878" url="?curid=1010430" title="Boccia at the 2004 Summer Paralympics">
<text>[[Boccia]] at the [[2004 Summer Paralympics]] took place in the Ano Liossia Olympic Hall in Athens. Contestants were categorised as follows:
*BC1: players with cerebral palsy, competing with the help of an aide, who can only adjust the playing chair and give a ball to the player.
*BC2: players with cerebral palsy not requiring an aide.
*BC3: players with a very severe locomotor dysfunction, using an assistive device and assisted by an aide, who will remain in the player&#x27;s box but who must keep his/her back to the court and eyes averted from play.
*BC4: players with other locomotor disabilities, without an aide.

