<doc id="1010502" wikidata="Q5687321" url="?curid=1010502" title="Hayu">
<text>The Hayus() are a member of the Kirat tribe speaking their own language, Wayu or Hayu. Little is known about them. They are Hindus by religion. According to the 2001 Nepal census, there are 1821 Hayu in the country, of which 70.29% were Hindus and 23.61% were animists.

The Hayu language has been documented by the linguist Boyd Michailovsky. The language currently appears in Wikipedia as &#x27;Vayu&#x27;.

