<doc id="1010589" wikidata="Q6941381" url="?curid=1010589" title="Music, Martinis and Misanthropy">
<text>Music, Martinis and Misanthropy is an album by Boyd Rice, released in 1990 by New European Recordings. It was recorded in Tokyo, Japan and Denver, Colorado between July 1989 and March 1990 and features several notable neofolk artists - Douglas P. (of Death in June), Tony Wakeford (of Sol Invictus), Rose McDowall (of Strawberry Switchblade) and Michael Moynihan and Bob Ferbrache of Blood Axis. Most of the music was arranged by Douglas P. in collaboration with Rice and Ferbrache.

This album was inspired by Rod McKuen&#x27;s spoken word albums and Jackie Gleason&#x27;s romantic recordings from the 1950s. The title and album cover are a tribute to Gleasons&#x27;s album, &quot;Music, Martinis, and Memories&quot;. The liner notes thank Anton LaVey, Rod McKuen, Ragnar Redbeard, Lee Hazlewood, Pat Purdy, Richard and Karen C., The Everly Brothers&#x27; Father, Walt Disney, Artie De Gobineau and &quot;Big&quot; Jim Huberty.

